00:11:52.539 --> 00:11:59.219
Another question was, does Corto support multi-format document rendering, meaning rendering as PDF,

00:11:59.219 --> 00:12:03.020
Word, and HTML all at the same time?

00:12:03.020 --> 00:12:04.380
It does.

00:12:04.419 --> 00:12:11.419
All you have to do is on your YAML, on the sort of front matter, on the first YAML block,

00:12:11.419 --> 00:12:17.179
instead of saying format types or format HTML, you can say format colon, add a new line and

00:12:17.179 --> 00:12:23.179
sort of start writing new things, and then HTML colon default, types colon default,

00:12:23.179 --> 00:12:27.500
doc X colon default, and then when Corto renders, it will render all of them.

00:12:27.500 --> 00:12:31.539
And as a side effect, if you do this on a website, you will get the HTML on the website

00:12:31.539 --> 00:12:35.020
and you get a sidebar on the column that gets you the links to the other formats to

00:12:35.020 --> 00:12:40.659
be sort of easily downloadable for people who need it.

00:12:40.659 --> 00:12:42.900
Thank you.

