resources enabled.

00:19:34.439 --> 00:19:41.300
So embed resources is a option in Cordo that effectively sort of takes all of the images,

00:19:41.300 --> 00:19:46.339
takes all of the links, like all of the resources that a webpage usually has that are in separate

00:19:46.339 --> 00:19:50.540
files and makes it into one big file, which is how PDF works, right?

00:19:50.540 --> 00:19:53.579
Just have this one file and you can share it with people.

00:19:53.579 --> 00:19:59.579
If you're generating an HTML, by default, Cordo will keep those files separate so that

00:19:59.579 --> 00:20:02.920
multiple files can share the same resources and that's more efficient.

00:20:02.920 --> 00:20:06.579
But if you want to be able to email it to someone or to just put it separately so that

00:20:06.579 --> 00:20:11.300
people don't need to have any sort of additional files, then you need to have embed resources.

00:20:11.300 --> 00:20:14.500
And so that's the main thing that I would consider.

00:20:14.500 --> 00:20:22.339
I would, in general, just lean on using PDF, either the type support or the PDF or text

00:20:22.339 --> 00:20:28.099
support for it, mostly because there's fewer chances for strange things to go wrong with

00:20:28.099 --> 00:20:33.859
HTML, which is generally meant to like live in a web server somewhere rather than be shared

00:20:33.859 --> 00:20:40.099
by email and sort of sending it around.

00:20:40.099 --> 00:20:45.739
I wanted to just share something really quickly before I forget to say it at the end.

