We really want to do that.

00:26:02.319 --> 00:26:03.880
That's something that Nitr supports.

00:26:03.880 --> 00:26:08.199
If you're running by Nitr by itself, you can ask for Nitr to use WebShot 2, which is a

00:26:08.199 --> 00:26:10.079
library in R to do it.

00:26:10.079 --> 00:26:13.800
But Quarto needs to support other engines like Jupyter and Julia.

00:26:13.839 --> 00:26:18.760
And so we currently don't support something that's generic across all the different engines.

00:26:18.760 --> 00:26:23.599
You can do it in Nitr, but you cannot do it in other formats easily.

00:26:23.599 --> 00:26:29.680
We certainly want to do it and hopefully we'll get to next year, but it takes quite a bit

